Cultivate Innovative and Leadership Abilities in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills and Professional Research 

課程概述 Course Description
       The course will introduce students potential sources of research evidences, including those of informal ones (e.g., news and social media on the Internet) and formal ones (e.g., peer-reviewed journals). Students will learn to evaluate  face validity of sources. The course will also introduce students the structures of typical scientific literature, including primary research articles and review articles. Students will have opportunities to dissect articles based on key concepts and elements. 
This course will use a small group setting with support from a teacher. In each class, an article in Chinese will be used as an example to introduce concepts, and then corresponding English article will be used as a comparison. This course will emphasize knowing the logic of scientific articles, instead of the knowledge of research method itself. By taking this course, students will be better prepared for the advanced EBP courses in their later college years.The course will introduce students potential sources of research evidences, including those of informal ones (e.g., news and social media on the Internet) and formal ones (e.g., peer-reviewed journals). Students will learn to evaluate  face validity of sources. The course will also introduce students the structures of typical scientific literature, including primary research articles and review articles. Students will have opportunities to dissect articles based on key concepts and elements. 
This course will use a small group setting with support from a teacher. In each class, an article in Chinese will be used as an example to introduce concepts, and then corresponding English article will be used as a comparison. This course will emphasize knowing the logic of scientific articles, instead of the knowledge of research method itself. By taking this course, students will be better prepared for the advanced EBP courses in their later college years.
    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Students will know potential sources of research evidences from different media.Student will learn to identify key information and evaluate face validity.Students will learn the structure of articles. 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Course orientation - Search for interest and discuss with classmates2Can we trust news media? - Identify key information in articles in public media, evaluate its validity3Two types of research papers containing two types of information - Primary vs. Review articles4Primary research articles – Abstract5Primary research articles – Introduction section (I)6Primary research articles – Introduction section (II)7Holiday8Primary research articles – Materials and Methods sections (I)9Primary research articles – Materials and Methods sections (II)10Midterm11Primary research articles – Results (I)12Primary research articles – Results (II)13Primary research articles – Discussion (I)14Primary research articles – Discussion (II)15Review articles – Abstract, introduction, and methods16Review articles – Results and discussion17How to proceed when reading a scientific paper / How to read reference18Final examination 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


